{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse and an attempt at restitution by partially paying back the embezzled funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of professional trust, a 10-year sentence as suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the amount stolen and the defendant's background. Balancing the need for deterrence with the potential for rehabilitation, a sentence of 6 months is appropriate to reflect the seriousness of the offense without being excessively punitive for a first-time offender.",
  "verdict": 6
}
